<section>
    <h2>Description</h2>
    <p>The <code>&lt;dt&gt;</code> element (definition term) specifies the term, name, or key in a <a href="/docs/elements/native/dl/"><code>&lt;dl&gt;</code></a> (definition list). It must be followed by one or more <a href="/docs/elements/native/dd/"><code>&lt;dd&gt;</code></a> elements that describe or define the term.</p>
    <p>By default, <code>&lt;dt&gt;</code> elements are styled with bold font weight to visually distinguish them from their descriptions.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>When to Use</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Glossary terms being defined</li>
      <li>Property names in metadata displays</li>
      <li>Question text in FAQ sections</li>
      <li>Label in key-value pairs</li>
      <li>Product attribute names</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>When Not to Use</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Outside of a <code>&lt;dl&gt;</code> element</li>
      <li>For regular list items &mdash; use <a href="/docs/elements/native/li/"><code>&lt;li&gt;</code></a></li>
      <li>For standalone bold text &mdash; use <code>&lt;strong&gt;</code> or <code>&lt;b&gt;</code></li>
      <li>For headings &mdash; use <code>&lt;h1&gt;</code>&ndash;<code>&lt;h6&gt;</code></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Basic Usage</h2>

    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/dt-basic.html" url="dt-basic.html" title="Basic definition terms" shadow></browser-window>

